{
  "texts": [
    "An internal DSL offers more flexibility: it is possible to customize each and every aspect of prompt creation, behavior and response, as well as using control flow and operations to implement complex calculations and decisionmaking processes.",
    "Nevertheless, this added flexibility can lead to increased complexity and a lack of portability, tying a prompt to a particular technology, architecture or AI model.While other frameworks offer a greater deal of control over the AI pipeline, they also add other layers of complexity that make prompt engineering more complex.",
    "We believe that Impromptu's features make it well-suited for creating and reusing prompts and offer extra capabilities (prompt execution and response validation) as added value that requires very little effort from users.",
    "Case studyIn order to illustrate some of the benefits of the modeldriven approach using Impromptu, we show how we are transforming the curated prompt template library of Lang-BiTe [66], a Python open-source tool 6 to identify and assess biases in LLMs, into our language.",
    "Although this is not a thorough empirical analysis of Impromptu's potential impact, we nevertheless present an example of an actual real-world application [67] and detail the major outcomes Impromptu provided for managing an extensive collection of prompts.In general, each prompt in LangBiTe's library is composed of different snippets, the combination of which defines a specific strategy to query an LLM."
  ]
}